1 notification services office can sustain operations demands,
2 support staff salaries, and maintain uninterrupted services
3 statewide.
4 The purpose of this Act is to repeal the statutory-
5 expenditure ceiling on the automated victim information and
6 notification system special fund.
7 SECTION 2. Section 353-136, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 "[-{•] §353-136 [-}-] Automated victim infozrmation and
10 notification system special fund; authorization of payment. (a)
11 There is established a special fund to be known as the automated
12 victim information and notification system special fund, to be
13 administered by the department. Interest and investment
14 earnings credited to the assets of the fund shall become part of
15 the fund. Any remaining balance in the fund at the end of any
16 fiscal year shall be carried over to the next fiscal year.
17 (b) Any item purchased by an in-state or out-of-state
18 inmate from a correctional facility commissary shall be subject
19 to a four per cent surcharge on the item's price. The proceeds
20 from the surcharge shall be deposited into the automated victim
21 information and notification system special fund.
